BinarySearchTrees

Class BinarySearchTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • BinarySearchTrees.BinarySearchTree

  • public class BinarySearchTree
extends java.lang.Object
    CSCI 333, Homework 6: Binary Search Trees. This class implements the methods used to modify and otherwise access the binary search tree including insertion, deletion, transversals, and other operations.

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      BinarySearchTree()
      Constructor for the binary search tree, sets it to be empty at first by setting the root to null and the size to 0.

        public BSTNode search(BSTNode node,

        Parameters:
        node - Current position in the binary search tree.
        searchKey - Key being searched for in the binary search tree.
        Returns:
        Node containing the key being searched for.

      • minimum

        public BSTNode minimum(BSTNode node)
        Transverses down the left side of the subtree until the bottom node is reached. The node at this position holds the smallest key and is returned.
        Parameters:
        node - Starting position in the binary search tree.
        Returns:
        The node containing the smallest key within the passed binary search tree.

      • maximum

        public BSTNode maximum(BSTNode node)
        Transverses down the right side of the subtree until the bottom node is reached. The node at this position hold the largest key and is returned.
        Parameters:
        node - Starting position in the binary search tree.
        Returns:
        The node containing the largest key within the passed binary search tree.
